    <!-- Constitution Section -->
    <section class="constitution-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="constitution-intro">
          <h2>The Party's Guiding Document</h2>
          <p>The UPC Constitution establishes the framework for the party's
            principles, structures, operations, and procedures. It embodies our
            commitment to democracy, social justice, national unity, and
            sustainable development.</p>
          <p>Last amended and approved by the National Delegates Conference on
            June 15, 2023.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="constitution-content">
          <div class="constitution-article">
            <h3>ARTICLE I: NAME, SYMBOLS, AND IDENTITY</h3>
            <h4>Section 1: Name and Status</h4>
            <p>The name of the party shall be "UGANDA PEOPLE'S CONGRESS" (UPC).
              The Party shall be a political organization registered under the
              laws of Uganda.</p>
            <h4>Section 2: Party Symbols</h4>
            <p>The official symbol of the Party shall be the open right palm
              with fingers pointing upwards. The Party colors shall be blue and
              red, symbolizing peace, strength, and courage.</p>
            <h4>Section 3: Party Motto</h4>
            <p>The Party motto shall be "For Peace, Unity, and Development."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="constitution-article">
            <h3>ARTICLE II: VISION, MISSION, AND CORE VALUES</h3>
            <h4>Section 1: Vision</h4>
            <p>To build a united, democratic, and prosperous Uganda where
              citizens live in peace and enjoy equal opportunities and social
              justice.</p>
            <h4>Section 2: Mission</h4>
            <p>To mobilize Ugandans towards achieving socio-economic
              transformation, political stability, and cultural harmony through
              democratic governance, sustainable development policies, and
              respect for human rights.</p>
            <h4>Section 3: Core Values</h4>
            <p>The Party shall be guided by the following core values:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Democracy and good governance</li>
              <li>National unity and integration</li>
              <li>Social justice and equality</li>
              <li>Economic empowerment and self-reliance</li>
              <li>Integrity and accountability</li>
              <li>Peace and security</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="constitution-article">
            <h3>ARTICLE III: OBJECTIVES</h3>
            <p>The objectives of the Party shall be:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>To promote national unity and integration across Uganda's
                diverse ethnic, religious, and cultural groups.</li>
              <li>To establish and maintain democratic governance systems at all
                levels of government.</li>
              <li>To advocate for and implement policies that promote social
                justice, equality, and human rights.</li>
              <li>To develop and implement sustainable economic policies that
                empower citizens and reduce poverty.</li>
              <li>To build strong institutions that enhance transparency,
                accountability, and efficient public service delivery.</li>
              <li>To promote environmental conservation and sustainable use of
                natural resources.</li>
              <li>To foster international cooperation for peace, security, and
                development.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
          <div class="constitution-article">
            <h3>ARTICLE IV: MEMBERSHIP</h3>
            <h4>Section 1: Eligibility</h4>
            <p>Membership of the Party shall be open to all Ugandan citizens who
              are 18 years and above, subscribe to the Party's vision, mission,
              and core values, and comply with the Party's Constitution and Code
              of Conduct.</p>
            <h4>Section 2: Categories of Membership</h4>
            <p>The Party shall have the following categories of membership:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Ordinary Members:</strong> Registered members who pay
                the prescribed membership fees.</li>
              <li><strong>Life Members:</strong> Members who pay a one-time life
                membership fee as prescribed by the National Executive
                Committee.</li>
              <li><strong>Honorary Members:</strong> Individuals who have made
                significant contributions to the Party or to national
                development, as determined by the National Executive Committee.</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Section 3: Rights and Responsibilities</h4>
            <p>All members shall have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Participate in Party activities and decision-making processes.</li>
              <li>Vote and be voted for in Party elections, subject to meeting
                eligibility criteria.</li>
              <li>Access information about Party activities and use of Party
                resources.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>All members shall have the responsibility to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Uphold and promote the Party's vision, mission, and core
                values.</li>
              <li>Comply with the Party's Constitution, Code of Conduct, and
                policies.</li>
              <li>Pay membership fees and other prescribed fees promptly.</li>
              <li>Participate actively in Party activities and programs.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="constitution-article">
            <h3>ARTICLE V: PARTY STRUCTURE</h3>
            <h4>Section 1: National Level</h4>
            <p>The Party shall have the following organs at the national level:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>National Delegates Conference (NDC):</strong> The
                supreme authority of the Party.</li>
              <li><strong>National Council (NC):</strong> The policy-making
                organ between NDC meetings.</li>
              <li><strong>National Executive Committee (NEC):</strong> The
                implementing organ of Party policies.</li>
              <li><strong>Parliamentary Caucus:</strong> Consists of all UPC
                Members of Parliament.</li>
              <li><strong>National Secretariat:</strong> The administrative
                organ headed by the Secretary-General.</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Section 2: Regional Level</h4>
            <p>The Party shall establish Regional Coordination Committees to
              coordinate Party activities within defined regions.</p>
            <h4>Section 3: District Level</h4>
            <p>The Party shall have the following organs at the district level:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>District Conference</li>
              <li>District Executive Committee</li>
              <li>District Secretariat</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Section 4: Constituency and Sub-county Levels</h4>
            <p>The Party shall have Executive Committees at the constituency and
              sub-county levels.</p>
            <h4>Section 5: Parish and Village Levels</h4>
            <p>The Party shall have Executive Committees at the parish and
              village levels.</p>
          </div>
